        <abstract>
            <p>Lyell has received compliments for letting readers draw own inferences [on species question]. Now feels he earlier did Lamarck injustice. [CD’s] substitution of variety-making power for volition [as in Lamarck] in some respects only a change of names.</p>
            <p>Thinks Huxley taking on too many responsibilities.</p>
        </abstract>
